SAPS members were conducting routine patrols when Sergeant Andries Mabena was fatally wounded. JOHANNESBURG Gauteng police say an officer has been shot dead in Jeppestown in Johannesburg. South African Police Service (SAPS) members were conducting vehicle and foot-patrols when they responded to information of a business robbery at a plastic shop.Police later spotted two suspects and a shootout ensued. Sergeant Andries Mabena was fatally wounded and the two men managed to escape.